into a white baking dish with blackberries coated in the same powder" class="wp-image-88799" srcset="https://glutenfreeonashoestring.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Gluten-free-blackberry-cobbler-step-4.jpg 1200w, https://glutenfreeonashoestring.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Gluten-free-blackberry-cobbler-step-4-500x500.jpg 500w, https://glutenfreeonashoestring.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Gluten-free-blackberry-cobbler-step-4-860x860.jpg 860w, https://glutenfreeonashoestring.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Gluten-free-blackberry-cobbler-step-4-150x150.jpg 150w, https://glutenfreeonashoestring.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Gluten-free-blackberry-cobbler-step-4-400x400.jpg 400w, https://glutenfreeonashoestring.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Gluten-free-blackberry-cobbler-step-4-300x300.jpg 300w, https://glutenfreeonashoestring.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Gluten-free-blackberry-cobbler-step-4-96x96.jpg 96w, https://glutenfreeonashoestring.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Gluten-free-blackberry-cobbler-step-4-378x378.jpg 378w, https://glutenfreeonashoestring.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Gluten-free-blackberry-cobbler-step-4-276x276.jpg 276w, https://glutenfreeonashoestring.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Gluten-free-blackberry-cobbler-step-4-600x600.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></figure>
</div>
</div>



<p><strong>Combine dry topping ingredients</strong><br>To make the topping, whisk the all purpose gluten free flour with xanthan gum, baking powder, baking soda, salt and 1/4 cup granulated sugar in a large mixing bowl. Avoid any pockets of leavening which can create a bitter taste. </p>



<p><strong>Add cold butter</strong><br>Slice very cold butter into thin shards and toss with a mixing spoon to coat them in the dry ingredients. These slices will scatter throughout the topping easily and expand to create a fluffy biscuit topping in the oven. If there are any thicker pieces of butter, press them with floured fingers to flatten them and avoid any pooling, leaking butter.</p>



<p><strong>Add cold buttermilk</strong><br>Create a well in the center of the dry ingredients and pour in cold buttermilk. This will make it easier to mix without handling the dough too much. </p>



<div class="wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-28f84493 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex">
