</div>



<div class="wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow">
<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1200" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%201200'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="blackberries and raspberries coated in white powder spread in an even layer in a square white baking dish" class="wp-image-88793" data-lazy-srcset="https://glutenfreeonashoestring.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Gluten-free-blackberry-cobbler-step-5.jpg 1200w, https://glutenfreeonashoestring.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Gluten-free-blackberry-cobbler-step-5-500x500.jpg 500w, https://glutenfreeonashoestring.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Gluten-free-blackberry-cobbler-step-5-860x860.jpg 860w, https://glutenfreeonashoestring.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Gluten-free-blackberry-cobbler-step-5-150x150.jpg 150w, https://glutenfreeonashoestring.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Gluten-free-blackberry-cobbler-step-5-400x400.jpg 400w, https://glutenfreeonashoestring.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Gluten-free-blackberry-cobbler-step-5-300x300.jpg 300w, https://glutenfreeonashoestring.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Gluten-free-blackberry-cobbler-step-5-96x96.jpg 96w, https://glutenfreeonashoestring.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Gluten-free-blackberry-cobbler-step-5-378x378.jpg 378w, https://glutenfreeonashoestring.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Gluten-free-blackberry-cobbler-step-5-276x276.jpg 276w, https://glutenfreeonashoestring.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Gluten-free-blackberry-cobbler-step-5-600x600.jpg 600w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://glutenfreeonashoestring.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Gluten-free-blackberry-cobbler-step-5.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1200" src="https://glutenfreeonashoestring.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Gluten-free-blackberry-cobbler-step-5.jpg" alt="blackberries and raspberries coated in white powder spread in an even layer in a square white baking dish" class="wp-image-88793" srcset="https://glutenfreeonashoestring.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Gluten-free-blackberry-cobbler-step-5.jpg 1200w, https://glutenfreeonashoestring.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Gluten-free-blackberry-cobbler-step-5-500x500.jpg 500w, https://glutenfreeonashoestring.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Gluten-free-blackberry-cobbler-step-5-860x860.jpg 860w, https://glutenfreeonashoestring.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Gluten-free-blackberry-cobbler-step-5-150x150.jpg 150w, https://glutenfreeonashoestring.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Gluten-free-blackberry-cobbler-step-5-400x400.jpg 400w, https://glutenfreeonashoestring.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Gluten-free-blackberry-cobbler-step-5-300x300.jpg 300w, https://glutenfreeonashoestring.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Gluten-free-blackberry-cobbler-step-5-96x96.jpg 96w, https://glutenfreeonashoestring.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Gluten-free-blackberry-cobbler-step-5-378x378.jpg 378w, https://glutenfreeonashoestring.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Gluten-free-blackberry-cobbler-step-5-276x276.jpg 276w, https://glutenfreeonashoestring.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Gluten-free-blackberry-cobbler-step-5-600x600.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></figure>
</div>
</div>



<p><strong>Scoop on the topping</strong><br>Use a large spring-loaded ice cream scoop or two large spoons to scoop 7 to 8 mounds of topping, about 3 tablespoons each. Position the mounts across the top of the berries in the baking dish next to one another without overlapping them. Keep them toward the center of the baking dish so they can spread toward the edges during baking.</p>



<p><strong>Bake until done</strong><br>Bake for 20 minutes at 375°F/190°C to get the topping to rise and start to brown and the berries to start to release their moisture quickly. Reduce the oven temperature to 350°F/176°C and bake for about another 20 minutes. The dish is done when the topping is baked all the way to the center, the berries are softened, and the tapioca starch has thickened the filling liquid into a syrup.</p>



